          <p class="section-intro">
            Work through these questions in order — they progress from Achieved through to
            Scholarship. Write your answers in the text areas, then reveal the model answers
            to compare. For the AI-marked question, submit your response for instant feedback.
          </p>

          <div class="question-section">
            <h3 class="question-section__title">Short Answer (Achieved)</h3>

            <div class="question-card">
              <div class="question-card__header">
                <span class="question-number">Q1</span>
                <span class="question-type-badge question-type-badge--short">Achieved</span>
              </div>
              <p class="question-text">
                Identify the primary environmental cue that triggers migration in most bird species
                and explain why this cue is more reliable than temperature.
              </p>
              <textarea class="answer-input answer-input--med" data-answer="1" placeholder="Write your answer here..."></textarea>
            </div>

            <div class="question-card">
              <div class="question-card__header">
                <span class="question-number">Q2</span>
                <span class="question-type-badge question-type-badge--short">Achieved</span>
              </div>
              <p class="question-text">
                Name the hormone secreted by the pineal gland and explain how its secretion pattern
                differs between long days and short days.
              </p>
              <textarea class="answer-input answer-input--med" data-answer="2" placeholder="Write your answer here..."></textarea>
